with Jay and Gloria.

135
00:05:32.999 --> 00:05:37.086  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
- I don’t like that guy.
- What? That’s–
You like everybody.

136
00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:40.047  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Not Jay.
Guy rubs me the wrong way.

137
00:05:40.131 --> 00:05:45.094  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:79.00% 
Every time I try to do
somethin’ nice, he makes
this cranky face, like–

138
00:05:45.178 --> 00:05:46.929  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Okay. Well, you know what?

139
00:05:47.013 --> 00:05:51.350  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I’m gonna chalk this up
to jet lag for you, because
it’s not like you at all, okay?

140
00:05:51.434 --> 00:05:54.312  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
You have to make an effort.
It’s my partner’s father.

141
00:05:54.396 --> 00:05:56.189  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Now, give me the growl
that means okay.

142
00:05:56.273 --> 00:05:58.357  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:75.93% 
[ Growls ]

143
00:05:56.273 --> 00:05:58.357  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Good.

144
00:05:58.441 --> 00:06:03.362  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
Did you know Walt
had a daughter he was
completely estranged from?

145
00:06:03.446 --> 00:06:07.325  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
His lawyer said she wouldn’t
even honor his last request to
toss his dog tags in the ocean.

146
00:06:07.409 --> 00:06:10.203  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:69.06% 
Can you imagine?

147
00:06:07.409 --> 00:06:10.203  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:84.23% 
Phil, do we really have to
go through this again?

148
00:06:10.287 --> 00:06:11.954  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I told you I would do
everything possible...

149
00:06:12.038 --> 00:06:15.249  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
to make sure that your skeleton
ends up in a science class
at a women’s college.

150
00:06:15.333 --> 00:06:17.376  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
No, it’s just sad.

151
00:06:17.460 --> 00:06:20.296  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
That’s half of what will
keep me going in my old age.

152
00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:23.424  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:70.50% 
Remembering all the good
times with the kids.

153
00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:23.424  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Oh.

154
00:06:23.508 --> 00:06:26.344  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
Teaching Luke
to ride his bike.

155
00:06:26.428 --> 00:06:28.972  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Haley at
the father-daughter dance.

156
00:06:30.640 --> 00:06:32.642  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
Taking Alex for
her first pony ride.

157
00:06:32.726 --> 00:06:34.936  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
You never took Alex
on a pony ride.

158
00:06:36.229 --> 00:06:37.939  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
Oh, right,
that was just me.

159
00:06:36.229 --> 00:06:37.939  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
Mm-hmm.

160
00:06:38.023 --> 00:06:41.526  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
But Alex and I went, um–
Oh, no, that was Haley.

161
00:06:41.610 --> 00:06:43.736  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:75.93% 
Mmm.

162
00:06:41.610 --> 00:06:43.736  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Huh.

163
00:06:43.820 --> 00:06:46.990  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Phil. Look, it’s Luke.
He’s going into Walt’s house.

164
00:06:50.076 --> 00:06:51.118  position:80.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Phil ]
Aw.

165
00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:53.412  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:75.93% 
He’s saying good-bye.

166
00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:53.412  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.66% 
[ Door Closes ]

167
00:06:53.496 --> 00:06:55.831  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
He just needed
a little time.

168
00:06:55.915 --> 00:06:59.961  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
That is so sweet
and so sad. Wow.

169
00:07:00.045 --> 00:07:03.256  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
He’s so much more sensitive
than I ever thought.

170
00:07:03.340 --> 00:07:05.466  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Sighs ]
They had a special bond.

171
00:07:05.550 --> 00:07:09.136  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I wouldn’t be surprised
if one day he wrote a book
like <i>Tuesdays With Morrie.</i>

172
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:12.432  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:69.06% 
[ Door Opens ]

173
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:12.432  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.23% 
I never read it. Did that
guy steal Morrie’s TV?

174
00:07:20.690 --> 00:07:23.776  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Now setting a course
for adventure.

175
00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:25.778  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
♪ Beep-boop-beep-bop
boop-boop-boop ♪

176
00:07:25.862 --> 00:07:29.574  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
I’ve had great experiences
with all my kids, but I–

177
00:07:29.658 --> 00:07:31.826  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
I might have fallen
behind a bit with Alex.

178
00:07:31.910 --> 00:07:33.494  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.67% 
My fault completely.

179
00:07:33.578 --> 00:07:36.497  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Adventure? We are
throwing dog tags into
an already polluted ocean...

180
00:07:36.581 --> 00:07:38.833  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
where they will probably
choke an otter.

181
00:07:38.917 --> 00:07:41.168  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
Eighty percent my fault.

182
00:07:41.252 --> 00:07:44.797  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Honey, we’re bringing closure
to a man’s life.

183
00:07:44.881 --> 00:07:46.507  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
We’ll hike up to
the scenic overlook–

184
00:07:46.591 --> 00:07:48.718  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
where apparently Walt
proposed to his wife–

185
00:07:48.802 --> 00:07:52.847  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
wait for the light to be
just right, say a few words,
share some memories.

186
00:07:52.931 --> 00:07:55.725  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
It’s kind of poetic.
Kind of Navaho.

187
00:07:55.809 --> 00:07:57.643  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Now you’re getting it.

188
00:07:57.727 --> 00:08:00.771  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
We’ll be sending him off
with a level of dignity that,
if we’re lucky,

189
00:08:00.855 --> 00:08:02.648  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
some day we’ll experience too.

190
00:08:02.732 --> 00:08:04.234  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
It’s called–

191
00:08:07.404 --> 00:08:08.738  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:89.67% 
Huh.

192
00:08:18.998 --> 00:08:22.543  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:69.06% 
[ Knocks ]

193
00:08:18.998 --> 00:08:22.543  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:84.23% 
Hey, what have you
got there? Walt’s old TV?

194
00:08:22.627 --> 00:08:25.004  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
He said that I could take
one thing after he died.

195
00:08:25.088 --> 00:08:26.672  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I wish he would
have said two things.

196
00:08:26.756 --> 00:08:28.758  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I would have taken that phone
with the big buttons.

197
00:08:28.842 --> 00:08:33.429  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
I bet you guys had some
really good times watching
this thing, right?

198
00:08:33.513 --> 00:08:35.765  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
No. I just wanted
a TV in my room.

199
00:08:37.392 --> 00:08:41.604  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
You know, Luke,
there might be a nicer way
to honor Walt’s memory.

200
00:08:41.688 --> 00:08:45.900  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
- What do you mean?
- Well, I mean, you guys
liked to garden.

201
00:08:45.984 --> 00:08:49.987  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
We could, uh– We could
take one of his flowers
and plant it in our yard.

202
00:08:50.071 --> 00:08:52.907  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:50.00%  line:75.93% 
And then every spring, when–

203
00:08:50.071 --> 00:08:52.907  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
[ Banging ]

204
00:08:52.991 --> 00:08:56.035  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:69.06% 
Ah, there we go.

205
00:08:52.991 --> 00:08:56.035  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.23% 
<i>[ TV Announcer,</i>
<i>Indistinct ]</i>

206
00:08:56.119 --> 00:08:59.205  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
Sweetie, how you feeling?

207
00:08:59.289 --> 00:09:01.707  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Are you sad?
Angry?

208
00:09:01.791 --> 00:09:05.252  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Confused? Frustrated?
You know, you can talk to me.

209
00:09:05.336 --> 00:09:08.047  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I know, but I can’t
see through you.
Could you scooch?

210
00:09:08.131 --> 00:09:11.801  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
No, no.
You know, this is not okay.
It’s going back.

211
00:09:11.885 --> 00:09:14.887  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:70.50% 
What? He said
I could pick one thing.

212
00:09:11.885 --> 00:09:14.887  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.66% 
This isn’t picking.

213
00:09:14.971 --> 00:09:16.555  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
It’s looting,
and it’s going back.

214
00:09:16.639 --> 00:09:18.766  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Oh! You are so mean.

215
00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:20.726  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
When Walt used to look through
those binoculars...

216
00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:23.813  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
and say,
"Your dad’s one lucky man,"
he was wrong.

217
00:09:26.441 --> 00:09:29.402  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:69.06% 
Hi, Haley.

218
00:09:26.441 --> 00:09:29.402  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.23% 
Hi. Stef, Sam,
this is Manny.

219
00:09:29.486 --> 00:09:31.654  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:69.06% 
What’s up, dude?

220
00:09:29.486 --> 00:09:31.654  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.23% 
Kitchen’s over there
and pool’s in the back.

221
00:09:31.738 --> 00:09:34.073  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
So where
are your parents?

222
00:09:31.738 --> 00:09:34.073  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.66% 
They’re not coming.

223
00:09:34.157 --> 00:09:37.284  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
I was told there’d
be a chaperone.

224
00:09:34.157 --> 00:09:37.284  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.66% 
There is. It’s you.

225
00:09:37.368 --> 00:09:38.911  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
My parents are totally
fine with it.

226
00:09:38.995 --> 00:09:43.749  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:79.00% 
Well, exits,
fire extinguisher,
burn kit.

227
00:09:43.833 --> 00:09:45.418  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Okay, let’s have some fun.

228
00:09:45.502 --> 00:09:48.421  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:73.67% 
<i>♪♪ [ Stereo: Rock ]</i>
 
I believe it was clear
the bedrooms are off-limits.

229
00:09:48.505 --> 00:09:52.509  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Young lady, I don’t think you’re
ready up here for what you’re
planning to do up there.

230
00:09:55.094 --> 00:09:57.304  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Sniffs, Groans ]
Not on my watch.

231
00:09:57.388 --> 00:09:59.516  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Scoffs ]

232
00:10:00.850 --> 00:10:02.935  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, this was a delicious
meal, Mitchell.

233
00:10:03.019 --> 00:10:06.439  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
I wish my wife could cook
a roast like this.

234
00:10:06.523 --> 00:10:09.108  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:70.50% 
You got a good ’un
there, Son.

235
00:10:06.523 --> 00:10:09.108  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.66% 
Well, I’m very lucky.

236
00:10:09.192 --> 00:10:12.027  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
Just like you and Mama:
never had a bad patch.

237
00:10:12.111 --> 00:10:13.946  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
Except the winter of ’85.
Remember that?

238
00:10:14.030 --> 00:10:18.618  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, I spent several nights
in the cow bed then. Hmm.

239
00:10:20.703 --> 00:10:23.038  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:69.06% 
Oh, here. Let me help you.

240
00:10:20.703 --> 00:10:23.038  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.23% 
No, no, no.
You sit– sit down.

241
00:10:23.122 --> 00:10:26.542  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:70.50% 
Let’s us guys catch up
here a little bit.

242
00:10:23.122 --> 00:10:26.542  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Yeah.

243
00:10:26.626 --> 00:10:29.712  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
<i>[ Jay ] I’ll tell you why</i>
<i>I don’t like that guy, and I</i>
<i>could never say this to Mitch.</i>

244
00:10:29.796 --> 00:10:33.549  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
He treats my son like
the wife in the relationship.
Always has.

245
00:10:33.633 --> 00:10:37.094  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Before we get to dessert,
I’ve got some presents here.

246
00:10:37.178 --> 00:10:39.013  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:50.00%  line:69.06% 
Oh, you didn’t need to, Dad.

247
00:10:37.178 --> 00:10:39.013  position:80.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:84.23% 
[ Gloria ]
<i>Ay.</i>

248
00:10:39.097 --> 00:10:41.348  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Love it.

249
00:10:41.432 --> 00:10:44.977  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, Merle,
thank you so much.

250
00:10:45.061 --> 00:10:48.314  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Look at this.
Oh, so elegant, huh?

251
00:10:48.398 --> 00:10:51.650  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, this is so sweet.
I think I might cry.

252
00:10:51.734 --> 00:10:53.319  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Don’t.

253
00:10:53.403 --> 00:10:54.945  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Dad, I’ve really
gotta get home–

254
00:10:55.029 --> 00:10:57.948  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I know, I know,
you gotta do homework.

255
00:10:58.032 --> 00:11:01.994  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
You can’t expect me to see a
sign that says "World’s Greatest
Milk Shake, 50 Miles"...

256
00:11:02.078 --> 00:11:03.829  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
and not drive to it.

257
00:11:03.913 --> 00:11:05.581  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
Sorry, sweetie.
Machine’s broken.

258
00:11:05.665 --> 00:11:07.082  position:45.00%,start  align:start size:50.00%  line:89.67% 
Huh.

259
00:11:07.166 --> 00:11:10.002  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
I just wanted a special day
with my daughter, you know?

260
00:11:10.086 --> 00:11:14.048  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
Like the time we gave
an old man a dramatic
send-off at the beach.

261
00:11:14.132 --> 00:11:18.844  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Or-Or the time we drove
a hundred miles for the world’s
greatest milk shake.

262
00:11:18.928 --> 00:11:20.930  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Call us when it
happens, Francine.

263
00:11:21.014 --> 00:11:22.598  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, could be
before you get home.

264
00:11:22.682 --> 00:11:24.517  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
I’m a week past
my due date as it is.

265
00:11:24.601 --> 00:11:26.477  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.67% 
What can I do for you?

266
00:11:26.561 --> 00:11:30.689  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
The time
we delivered a baby.

267
00:11:30.773 --> 00:11:32.691  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
We were the only ones there,
and she was so close.

268
00:11:32.775 --> 00:11:35.194  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
The sound of a pin dropping
could induce labor.

269
00:11:35.278 --> 00:11:37.530  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:75.93% 
